  "prob_desc_description": "You are given a sequence $$$a_1, a_2, \\dots, a_n$$$ consisting of $$$n$$$ integers.You can choose any non-negative integer $$$D$$$ (i.e. $$$D \\ge 0$$$), and for each $$$a_i$$$ you can:  add $$$D$$$ (only once), i. e. perform $$$a_i := a_i + D$$$, or  subtract $$$D$$$ (only once), i. e. perform $$$a_i := a_i - D$$$, or  leave the value of $$$a_i$$$ unchanged. It is possible that after an operation the value $$$a_i$$$ becomes negative.Your goal is to choose such minimum non-negative integer $$$D$$$ and perform changes in such a way, that all $$$a_i$$$ are equal (i.e. $$$a_1=a_2=\\dots=a_n$$$).Print the required $$$D$$$ or, if it is impossible to choose such value $$$D$$$, print -1.For example, for array $$$[2, 8]$$$ the value $$$D=3$$$ is minimum possible because you can obtain the array $$$[5, 5]$$$ if you will add $$$D$$$ to $$$2$$$ and subtract $$$D$$$ from $$$8$$$. And for array $$$[1, 4, 7, 7]$$$ the value $$$D=3$$$ is also minimum possible. You can add it to $$$1$$$ and subtract it from $$$7$$$ and obtain the array $$$[4, 4, 4, 4]$$$.",
